# {{CLIENT_NAME}} — Cursor agent rules

## Before any task
Always read .agent/CONTEXT.md before starting any work.
If the file is missing or empty, alert the user before proceeding.

## Session start
When the user says "start session", "let's start", or "begin session":
Run the skill defined in .agent/skills/start-session.md

## Session end
When the user says "end session", "wrap up", or "closing session":
Run the skill defined in .agent/skills/end-session.md

## Mode A logging
When the user says "log this", "log mode a", or "log quick task":
Run the skill defined in .agent/skills/log-mode-a.md

## Standing rules
Always apply the rules in .agent/instructions.md for the duration of the session.

## JIRA
Reference tickets as {{JIRA_PROJECT_KEY}}-[number]. Always check current-sprint.md before
starting any task to confirm it is in scope for the active sprint.

## Commits
Never commit directly to main.
Suggest commit messages in format: "session: YYYY-MM-DD · [summary] [skip ci]"
Wait for user confirmation before committing.
